html.htmlText:
Welcome to BoHo Farm House—a 3 bedroom + 3 ensuite bathroom, 8-acre luxurious haven in the scenic Hamlet of Accord, Hudson Valley.
Scandinavian style, vaulted wood ceilings, heated pool, screened porch, and serene stream-side gazebo, this meticulously designed retreat offers stunning country views from every angle, a chef's kitchen, and perfect proximity to amazing hiking, skiing, restaurants, farms, breweries, and local favorites.
Experience the pinnacle of style, luxury and tranquility.

1 / 1

Escape to BoHo Farm House, a newly renovated, luxurious retreat in the Hamlet of Accord, inspired by years of hosting guests at our film/photo studio and managing multiple homes. Designed with love, our haven is the ideal destination for any season to getaway with friends, a romantic escape, or a memorable family vacation.
We are an animal friendly property with a fully fenced in area for your pets to enjoy and charge a small additional fee for their stay. ($100)
This home effortlessly blends Scandinavian/Boho style with a mid-century ranch, offering a warm and inviting ambiance during the cozy seasons. Vaulted whitewash wood ceilings create an airy feel, and the decor exudes modern yet comfy charm. Enjoy natural light flooding the open living spaces, offering picturesque views of the snow-covered 8-acre property in winter & cozy up by the fire after a day skiing at Belleayre, Hunter or Wyndham.

Experience culinary heaven in the chef's kitchen at BoHo Farm House. Equipped with top-of-the-line appliances and ample counter space, the chef's kitchen is perfect for creating hearty meals during the colder months. Let us know if you're interested in a private chef, cooking lessons, or meal planning with locally sourced groceries before you arrive to make your winter stay even more delightful.

Enjoy the serene beauty of our property during fall and winter. Take leisurely strolls through the snow-covered landscape, or cozy up indoors with a good book while admiring the breathtaking views, or enjoy a firepit on the terrace or by the stream. BoHo Farm House is a sanctuary of relaxation, providing the perfect setting to unwind.

BoHo Farm House's prime location ensures you're never far from the best the Hudson Valley has to offer during fall and winter. Explore charming towns like Stone Ridge, Kerhonkson, High Falls, and Rosendale, which come alive with holiday festivities. Indulge in farm-to-table dining experiences, browse unique shops, and immerse yourself in the thriving arts and music scene. The historic city of Kingston, with its festive lights and winter markets, and incredible resturants and shopping is also within a 30-minute drive.

For outdoor enthusiasts, BoHo Farm House is a gateway to winter adventure. Embark on scenic hikes in nearby Minnewaska Park, the Scenic Rail Trail or many other hikes to experience the beauty of the landscape. Immerse yourself in nature's wonders as you traverse snow-covered trails and take in awe-inspiring vistas. Ski or snowboard at Bellearye, Hunter or Wyndham, all within a comfortable and scenic drive.

Discover local delights just minutes away. Indulge in exquisite produce at Saunderskill Farms & Accord Market, enjoy craft brews at Arrowood Brewery, or savor hearty comfort food at Ollie's Pizzeria. Families will delight in nearby destinations like Kelder's Farm, Skatetime, Inness, Westwind Orchard, and Stone Hill's Farmhouse, providing endless winter activities, food and entertainment.

At BoHo Farm House, we've created an oasis of luxury and relaxation. Whether you seek tranquility or adventure, this property offers the perfect balance for your desired fall and winter escape.

Our home is your home. We hope to attract like minded people who share similar values and are curious. We want your experience to be one you will want to repeat over and over.

We will continue to add more features and services and would love you to be part of creating our little utopia through your personal requests.

Our goal is to share the beauty of our environment, and provide a sanctuary for you to feel any stress you have experienced in the lead up to your trip evaporate when you enter our space.

As we welcome winter, we'd like to inform you that the colder weather sometimes draws some uninvited guests such as field mice and bugs into our homes. Please rest assured that these little visitors are harmless and do not pose any health risks.

We have taken natural preventive measures to minimize their presence, but if you happen to spot one, kindly understand that it's a part of the seasonal transition. Our team is always ready to assist, and your comfort and safety remain our top priorities.

Our longer term goal is to build a sustainable & regenerative mini farm with vegetables and herbs you can pick from our veggie garden and surroundings. Additionally, we will use the barns and fields to host rescue animals like we do at our other home in Accord.

Welcome to Accord, NY, a serene and picturesque destination nestled in the heart of the breathtaking Hudson Valley. Known for its tranquil atmosphere and natural beauty, Accord offers a perfect retreat for those seeking relaxation and rejuvenation.

As you arrive in Accord, you'll be greeted by lush green landscapes, rolling hills, and charming country roads. The area is renowned for its scenic hiking trails, making it an outdoor enthusiast's paradise. Lace up your boots and explore the captivating Shawangunk Ridge, where you'll discover stunning vistas, hidden waterfalls, and an abundance of wildlife.

From roller skating, skiing to vintage shopping, breweries and "cideries," there is plenty to do and see for those who are more social.

For those seeking a slower pace, Accord's peaceful charm extends to its local farms and orchards. Immerse yourself in the region's agricultural heritage by visiting charming farmers' markets and picking your own fresh produce, from crisp apples to succulent berries. Indulge in the farm-to-table culinary scene, where you can savor delectable meals crafted from locally sourced ingredients.

Accord also boasts a vibrant arts and culture scene. Discover unique galleries and artisanal shops that showcase the talents of local artists. Attend cultural & community events and festivals, and live music that celebrate the area's rich heritage, providing a glimpse into its vibrant spirit.

html.htmlText:
We want our guests to enjoy our property, but we have the following rules in place to protect our home and the environment.

Conservation of Energy: To ensure the efficient operation of the air-conditioner and minimize energy usage, kindly close all windows and doors when the air-conditioner is running. Feel free to use the fans and enjoy the cross breeze when the windows are open, except in extreme conditions.

Pool Safety: Please never, ever leave children unattended at anytime and prevent children who are unable to swim to be in the vicinity of the pool without constant supervision from a responsible and sober adult.

Pool Safety for Creatures: Please be mindful of the well-being of creatures around the pool area. When the pool is unattended, make sure to use the animal rescue pads provided to prevent any frogs, salamanders, or other small critters from accidentally entering the pool and potentially drowning.

No Guns or Hunting Allowed: For the preservation of the property's peaceful environment, we kindly request that no hunting activities take place on the premises. This prohibition also includes pets with hunting instincts. Let's cherish and respect the natural surroundings.

Care for the Home and Prompt Reporting of Damages: We invite you to treat our home with the same care and respect as you would your own. While accidents can occur, we appreciate your cooperation in reporting any breakages or damages promptly. This helps us maintain the quality experience for every guest.

Thank you for your understanding and cooperation.

* For a full set of house rules please look in the House guide - Info - Saftey Info and Rules - General House Rules

content.htmlText: Jeffersonville is a charming older village nestled in the Western part of the Sullivan County Catskills. You will see that Jeffersonville’s Main Street (Route 52) is loaded with entrepreneurial spirit offering an eclectic mix of shops, restaurants and businesses. Conveniently located near Bethel Woods Center for the Arts, the Woodstock Museum and the beautiful, scenic and recreational Delaware River. html.htmlText:
Service animals aren’t pets, so there’s no need to add them here.

Traveling with an emotional support animal? Check out our accessibility policy.

This little A-frame is a mid century dream nestled among the trees in the Pocono Mountains of Northeastern Pennsylvania and is within a few minutes walk to the lake.

Beautifully and loving curated, filled with mid- century furniture, lots of art, books and records.

A highlight of the cabin is the upstairs bathroom, featured in Condé Nast, Houzz and West Elm, it's a Pinterest dream come true. Come take a soak in our beautiful soaker tub among the trees.

2 hours from NYC.

There’s nothing quite like an A-frame and the instant we stepped foot on this houses original shag carpet we knew she was special, make sure to follow us on Social Media
@cabinvibes

Though we bought the house with the intention of renting we found it hard to part with, and after 2 years of planning and renovations we’ve finally taken the plunge. We’ve put a lot of time and effort into making this cabin truly special and we love nothing more, than sitting quietly on the deck watching the leaves turn or building a fire on a slow winter evening.

We have a full chefs kitchen, with hardwood teak counter tops and a double farmhouse sink along with dishwasher and Nespresso machine. We have dining table for 6 people. (A fold away outdoor dining table can also be utilized if wanting to eat outside)

The master suite is located at the back of the Cabin, with a private entrance onto the back porch, it also has its own staircase to the bathroom with a view. Upstairs we have our second bedroom with queen bed and 4 skylights overlooking trees. Downstairs we have an additional 3rd bedroom with a queen bed. Just note when the house is at max capacity (6 people) the 3rd bedroom will be walkthrough and those in the master suite will need to use the private entrance.

The community offers some great amenities, from the 2 lakes and 2 pools, tennis, vollyball, mini golf and we even have our own tiny ski hill and lift! There is an Art center where you can paint pottery and do array of different crafts, a gym (located in the north section) there is sauna in the changing rooms which AMAZING! basketball courts and a golf course. Another quick note, because this is a vacation and lake community you will have neighboring cabins, it’s still a private and large secluded lot, but if you are looking for something in the middle of nowhere without any neighboring cabins this is something to keep in mind.



There are two super cute towns, Hawley and Honesdale around 25 mins away from the cabin, which boast many coffee shops, Antique stores, restaurants, Railroad museums (great for children) these will be listed in our handbook.

We also have outdoor seating on the front and wrap around benches on a larger back deck with a fire pit, perfect for late night ghost stories.

Included: High speed internet, 140 channels, Netflix, Hulu and Amazon prime.

Guests will be given passes to use the nearby beach and pools and other amenities.

The lake is a few minutes walk from the house. Perfect for an evening stroll to watch the sunset.

You will be given membership passes by the community upon arrival. All guests will be registered with community and guests must check in with the Hideout upon arrival where you will get individual amenities badges and car passes (the community is gated) A renters form will be emailed to you to fill out prior to your trip this is necessary to gain entry to the community.

Pools are outside and m only open in the summer months. Lake and beach areas are open year round.

There is Nest camera located at the front of the cabin, as a safety precaution. We only check the camera to see if there is a car in the driveway to confirm a guests has arrived or departed. We actively respect your privacy during your trip.

html.htmlText:
the number one rule of the house is to leave it like you found it:) 
- We recently decided to welcome dogs to the cabin since we’ve had some excellent experiences so far and we know they are part of the family. All animals, must be pre approved and discussed before trip. Dogs must be under 60lbs. One dog per booking. 
-if you are staying for more then 2 weeks please water the house plants once a week      -you will be required to fill out a renters form which goes to our community registration. Without this you will not be permitted to enter the community. This needs to be submitted within 3 business days of your arrival.

-please be mindful of my neighbors when hanging out by the fire pit or on the deck at night (for sure you can talk and laugh like normal  mostly I just mean don’t blast music : )

-fire works are NOT allowed in my community, obviously there are lots of trees and no one wants their house to burn down lol. 

-please monitor the outdoor fire pit do not leave unattended.

-no smoking in the house. If smoking outside please make sure dispose of cigarette butts. 

- just a reminder that there are no animals allowed unless agreed upon beforehand.
 
-If you are going to fish just make sure you have a current PA license.

-There is a Canoe located under the back deck, you are welcome to use it. There are ratchets straps and pads to help attach to your car. 

-There is a Nest Camera located at the front of the house, this camera monitors the drive way. We actively respect our guests privacy, they are only checked once to make sure guests have arrived and we do not monitor cameras during your stay. 

-If you notice anything broken or anything you think needs maintence please don’t be afraid to let me know. We understand accidents happen and we do our best to keep everything perfect for you, but sometimes no one lets us know and what we don’t know we can’t fix. We’ll do our best to address any issues. 

Check out rules.

-  turn out all the lights  

-turn on ceiling fan

- close up any windows 
-clean out ash from fireplace and/or grill if you used them. Make sure its cooled first. 

Please take all your bags of trash to the hideout trash receptacles on you way home. It is located just across from the North Beach and basketball courts. You can also take any unwanted trash if you fill the outdoor cans anytime between 8am and 8pm everyday. Animals will get in your trash if it is left outside the can - we learned the hard way hehe. There’s definitely a family of raccoons 🦝 around.
There is a fee of $10 per bag for any left trash per my cleaning company.    

- please do not leave any dirty dishes in the sink and load up and start the dishwasher before you leave so it has time to finish for our next guest :) 

- please make sure to put away the games neatly for the next guests. Had few disasters stuffed back into the box and we tend to lose the tiny parts when this happens, thank you in advance! ;) 

- Drop keys back into lockbox  :)


---------------------------

-The house is already stocked with sheets blankets towels and pretty much all the things you will need. (There are extra blankets in the closets)

-The fire place at the house is super easy but if the smoke seems like it’s coming in make sure the flute is open. If the temps outside are warm you may find smoke coming into the house because it can’t rise so if this happens try again later when it cools off. 

That's all I can think of please don't hesitate to text me with questions if I don’t answer fast enough on Airbnb!

Have a great time!  

Xx

Relax in tranquility and scenic beauty from your own porch! Surrounded by state land just minutes from numerous hiking trails and waterfalls in promised land state park. Enjoy a dip in one of the nearby lakes or toasty fire on a cold night inside by the wood stove.

The space
The house is situated in a small wooded community 10mins from promised land state park with public access to hiking trails, docks, a beach, fishing, canoe and kayak rentals, and waterfalls. It's only a 25 min drive from Lake Wallenpaupack, and close to numerous quaint little towns, state forests, antique stores, local markets, and 15 min from skytop for skiing and snow tubing. Inside you will find a wood burning fire place, Wi-Fi, record player with record collection, board games, fully stocked kitchen, linens and towels, comfortable beds, and modern furniture.

The space is well-suited for a couple, a small family, or up to 4 friends.

My fully-furnished 2-BR cabin is located only 90 miles from Manhattan in the Pocono lake region. Around the area you can find skiing, hiking, tubing, waterfalls, state forests, antique stores, farm stands, and local markets. The community is packed full of soaring trees, boulders, and streams--and also cardinals, turkeys, foxes, and lots of deer who often laze around in my yard : ) A fire pit, back deck, outdoor seating and grill complete the outdoor experience.

Inside, the fire place fills the cabin with coziness and warmth. Features and amenities include ceiling fans, electric baseboard heaters in every room, High Speed Internet/Wi-Fi, 60 inch smart tv, record player with record collection, board games, fully stocked kitchen, linens and towels, beach towels, lawn chairs, comfortable beds, and modern furniture.

The space is well-suited for a couple, a small family, or a few friends. Both the master bedroom and upstairs loft room have queen-size beds with dressers and closets to store your things.

This tiny home is situated in a 40 acre artist preserve containing large open fields with all kinds of wildlife (deer, turkeys, birds and eagles) as well as 3 lakes. The largest lake is great for swimming, fishing, rowing and be sure to feel replenished by the natural beauty this property has to offer. So if your are from the city and need some nature in your life then look no further!

The property was developed by a masterful artist who transformed this property from what used to be a duck farm into an artist studio preserve.

If your an art enthusiast.. then this an amazing place to experience!

html.htmlText:
A modern, private cabin secluded within a private 19 acres, just 90 miles away from New York City ! This stunning home was designed by Sundial Studios Architecture & Design, and was featured both within Dwell Magazine (google: wabi sabi weekend cabin) and the NY Times (google: haiku of a home). This 3 bedroom 2 bath cabin was developed in response to the beautiful landscape it is placed within and is surrounded by forest and wildlife, overlooking a pond.

Follow us on Instagram - @pond.place

WiFi / Ducted A/C & Central Heating / Well-Behaved Dogs Welcome

Master Bedroom: Queen Bed
Bedroom 2: Full Bed
Bedroom 3: Twin Bunk Bed
Please note that this is a small cabin, and is appropriate for a maximum of 4 adults and 2 children (under 12 or so), as the bunk beds are suitable for child sized bodies.

INDOOR SPACE: Modern interior with open vaulted ceiling and exposed beams, wood-burning stove (wood provided), ducted air conditioning/heating system, Sonos sound system, custom designed millwork, lofted play area, book & games collection, and spectacular forest and pond views from the living room areas.

OUTDOOR SURROUNDINGS: Forested landscape with a private pond fed by a small waterfall, picnic table & fire pits, tree swings, private and secluded location, surrounding forest views, charcoal grill (charcoal not provided).

KITCHEN: Fully equipped, drip coffeemaker, tea kettle, cooking basics & spices.

GENERAL: Linens & towels, complimentary toiletries, washer/dryer. There is a Pack 'N Play available upon request.

PARKING: Gravel driveway with plenty of room for a few vehicles.

This property has 4 exterior security cameras overlooking the driveway, pond, and entry doors. All cameras except the driveway cam are disarmed at guest check in, and then turned back on at checkout. All cameras face outwards, and do not look into the interior spaces.
We keep a handful of cabinets and a storage room locked, but other than this the house and property are open to explore.

We have the driveway plowed in the wintertime, but guests should have a AWD or 4WD vehicle to access the property during snow season.

There is a Sullivan County burn ban every spring from mid March through until mid May, and no open fires are permitted during this time. Feel free to use the wood stove and outdoor barbeque, but no open fires are permitted in either of the outdoor fire pits.

- NOTE: This property sleeps a maximum of 4 adults and 2 children.

- Well behaved dogs are allowed.  Please make sure to pick up after them.

- No dogs are allowed on the furniture.  Please bring your own sheets to place over top the sofas if you expect your pet will jump up on them.

- No events, parties, large gatherings, or photo or film shoots are permitted.  No additional guests are allowed outside of the original reservation request, unless otherwise submitted and approved.  A charge of $400 will be applied to each and every unapproved guest per day of reservation.  Please don't exceed the approved guest count, and be honest about the number of people in your group.

- In the wintertime, an AWD or 4WD vehicle should be used to access the property.

- In the wintertime, please don't heat the cabin to over 80 degrees, and in the summertime, please don't run the air conditioning to less then 68 degrees.  And please, please, please do not run the heat or air conditioning and leave the doors wide open. 

- Please take care when playing music with the big doors open, especially after dark. While the cabin feels very isolated, the sound carries and we ask that you respect our neighbors

- We have a small beach area at the pond, but do not allowing swimming or fishing.  Please stay off the ice in the Winter.

- There is county wide burn ban every Spring from mid March thru to mid May.  We do not allow fires in the outdoor fire pits during this time.  

- Please do not make large outdoor fires, and do not leave them unattended.

- Keep all automobiles in the gravel driveway.  The other vehicle paths on the property are from a small utility vehicle we use for maintenance, which is much smaller than a car.

- Please supervise children within the garden, at the beach, and at the play area over in the far woods.

- Prospective guests must be at least 25 years old to book 

- Additional fees and taxes may apply 

- Photo ID may be required upon check-in

htmlDescription.htmlText:
A modern, private cabin secluded within a private 19 acres, just 90 miles away from New York City ! This stunning home was designed by Sundial Studios Architecture & Design, and was featured both within Dwell Magazine (google: wabi sabi weekend cabin) and the NY Times (google: haiku of a home). This 3 bedroom 2 bath cabin was developed in response to the beautiful landscape it is placed within and is surrounded by forest and wildlife, overlooking a pond.

Follow us on Instagram - @pond.place

The space
WiFi / Ducted A/C & Central Heating / Well-Behaved Dogs Welcome

Master Bedroom: Queen Bed
Bedroom 2: Full Bed
Bedroom 3: Twin Bunk Bed
Please note that this is a small cabin, and is appropriate for a maximum of 4 adults and 2 children (under 12 or so), as the bunk beds are suitable for child sized bodies.

INDOOR SPACE: Modern interior with open vaulted ceiling and exposed beams, wood-burning stove (wood provided), ducted air conditioning/heating system, Sonos sound system, custom designed millwork, lofted play area, book & games collection, and spectacular forest and pond views from the living room areas.

OUTDOOR SURROUNDINGS: Forested landscape with a private pond fed by a small waterfall, picnic table & fire pits, tree swings, private and secluded location, surrounding forest views, charcoal grill (charcoal not provided).

KITCHEN: Fully equipped, drip coffeemaker, tea kettle, cooking basics & spices.

GENERAL: Linens & towels, complimentary toiletries, washer/dryer. There is a Pack 'N Play available upon request.

PARKING: Gravel driveway with plenty of room for a few vehicles.

This property has 4 exterior security cameras overlooking the driveway, pond, and entry doors. All cameras except the driveway cam are disarmed at guest check in, and then turned back on at checkout. All cameras face outwards, and do not look into the interior spaces.

Guest access
We keep a handful of cabinets and a storage room locked, but other than this the house and property are open to explore.

Other things to note
We have the driveway plowed in the wintertime, but guests should have a AWD or 4WD vehicle to access the property during snow season.

There is a Sullivan County burn ban every spring from mid March through until mid May, and no open fires are permitted during this time. Feel free to use the wood stove and outdoor barbeque, but no open fires are permitted in either of the outdoor fire pits.
